properties.Name: EquifaxBusinessCreditIndustryReport
properties.Description: This table details open, non-financial accounts with a date reported within 24 months of inquiry.

Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX IDâ„¢ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description: Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: EquifaxFinancialAccountTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Equifax Financial Account Type.

Columns.Name: EquifaxPaymentTermId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Equifax Payment Term.

Columns.Name: DateOpened
Columns.Description: Date Opened/Years Sold refers to when the overall supplier/customer relationship was initiated.

Columns.Name: DateReported
Columns.Description: Date Reported refers to the most recent data submission received from the contributing data source

Columns.Name: YearsSold
Columns.Description: Date Opened/Years Sold refers to when the overall supplier/customer relationship was initiated.

Columns.Name: DateOfLastSale
Columns.Description: Date of Last Sale refers to the last reported date that goods were shipped or service was provided.

Columns.Name: HighCreditAmount
Columns.Description: High Credit refers to the highest reported balance from a supplier.

Columns.Name: CurrentCreditLimitAmount
Columns.Description: Current Credit Limit refers to the current credit limit reported.

Columns.Name: BalanceAmount
Columns.Description: Total reported balance including any past due amount.

Columns.Name: PastDueAmount
Columns.Description: Total amount past due from each aging category.

Columns.Name: AgingCat1
Columns.Description: Aging Category 1: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 1 period. Most creditors view Category 1 as 1-30 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCat2
Columns.Description: Aging Category 2: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 2 period. Most creditors view Category 2 as 31-60 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCat3
Columns.Description: Aging Category 3: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 3 period. Most creditors view Category 3 as 61-90 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCat4
Columns.Description: Aging Category 4: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 4 period. Most creditors view Category 4 as 91-120 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCat5
Columns.Description: Aging Category 5: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 5 period. Most creditors view Category 5 as 120+ days past due.

Columns.Name: 24MonthHistory
Columns.Description:
The 24-month history grid contains consecutive payment performance codes for the 60 months prior to the most recent date reported

Ex:
- 000100/010010  BBBBB/BBBBB

Columns.Name: ActiveAccountIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the account is active.

Columns.Name: PaymentAmount
Columns.Description: The payment amount.

Columns.Name: LastPaymentAmount
Columns.Description: The last payment amount.

Columns.Name: LastPaymentDate
Columns.Description: The last payment date.

Columns.Name: SecuredIndicator
Columns.Description:
Indicates that the account is secured.

Ex:
- Secured

Columns.Name: NumberOfGuarantors
Columns.Description: The number of guarantors.

Columns.Name: CurrentStatus
Columns.Description: The overall payment performance status of the most recently reported period.

Columns.Name: DateReportedDateOpenedOrYearsSold
Columns.Description: Date Reported refers to the most recent data submission received from the creditor; Date Opened or Years Sold refers to when the overall supplier/customer relationship was initiated.

Columns.Name: DateOfLastClosedSale
Columns.Description:
Date of Last Sale refers to the last reported date that goods were shipped or service
was provided.

Columns.Name: PaymentTerms
Columns.Description: Payment Terms is the payment due date agreed upon by the creditor and business.

Columns.Name: HighClosedCreditAmount
Columns.Description: High Credit refers to the highest reported balance from a creditor.

Columns.Name: CurrentClosedCreditAmount
Columns.Description: Current and Original Credit Limit refers to the credit limit at the most recently reported date or when the account was first opened.

Columns.Name: OriginalCreditAmount
Columns.Description: Original Credit Limit refers to the credit limit at the most recently reported date or when the account was first opened.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory1
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 1 period. Most creditors view Category 1 as 1-30 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory2
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 2 period. Most creditors view Category 2 as 31-60 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory3
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 3 period. Most creditors view Category 3 as 61-90 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory4
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 4 period. Most creditors view Category 4 as 91-120 days past due.

Columns.Name: AgingCategory5
Columns.Description: The dollar amount that is past due for the creditor's category 5 period. Most creditors view Category 5 as 120+ days past due.

Columns.Name: 60MonthHistoryGrid
Columns.Description:
The 60-month history grid contains consecutive payment performance codes for the 60 months prior to the most recent date reported. The far left position in the grid represents the previous month's overall account payment status.

where Current Status Descriptions:

B Unknown, which may indicate that the credit relationship did not exist before this time period.
C Account has been reported as closed.
0 Current
S Slow
1 Slow Up to 30
2 Slow Up to 60
3 Slow Up to 90
4 Slow Up to 120
5 Slow 121+
6 Collection
7 Non-accrual account
8 Repossession/Foreclosure
9 Charge-Off

Columns.Name: AccountComments
Columns.Description: Additional information provided by the creditor.

Columns.Name: ClosedBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: Balance refers to the total reported balance including any past due amount.

Columns.Name: ClosedPastDueAmount
Columns.Description: Past Due Amount refers to total delinquent dollars.
